<div>
	<i><p class="recipe name">
	Rainbow Cupcakes
	</p></i>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-sx-4">
<div class="rainbowphoto">
	<img src="rainbow.jpg" Width="300" height="200" style="position:absolute; top:650px; left: 100px; border-radius:20px;">
</div>
<div class="ingredientlist">
<div class="col-xs-3">
	<p1> Ingredients </p1>
	<ul class="Ingredients">
		<li class="rainbowingredients">225g Butter</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">475g sugar</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">5 egg whites</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">1 tablespoon vanilla essence</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">375g plain flour</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">4 teaspoons baking powder</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">125ml milk, warmed to room temperature</li>
		<li class="rainbowingredients">Gel food colouring in rainbow colours: Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Purple</li>
	</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div>
	<div class="col-xs-5">
	<p2> Method </p2>
		<ol class="Method">
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Preheat oven to 175C</li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Cream the butter and sugar together until smooth and light in colour. Then add in the egg whites and vanilla. </li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Mix the flour, salt and baking powder in a separate bowl.</li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Add the dry ingredients and milk to the creamed mixture.</li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Separate the cake mix into six separate bowls and colour each bowl with a separate colouring, mixing until the colours are fully combined</li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Add a thin layer of each mixture to cupcake cases, beginning with purple and working back to red.</li>
			<li class="rainbowmethod">Bake for 18-20 minutes.</li>
		</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div>
	<table class="icing_rainbow">


